<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="608" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="11.[789,1381,650,1073]" pageId="11" pageNumber="608">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[789,945,650,679]" pageId="11" pageNumber="608">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Thomas, 1906" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1906" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Lophuromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="11" pageNumber="608" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="aquilus" subSpecies="brunneus">Lophuromys aquilus brunneus Thomas, 1906</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation pageId="11" pageNumber="608">“Manno, Jimma, [South Ethiopia]. Alt. 4200’ [= 1280 m].”</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="608" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[789,1381,650,1073]" pageId="11" pageNumber="608">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1906" box="[791,1069,768,797]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Lophuromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="11" pageNumber="608" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brunneus">Lophuromys brunneus</taxonomicName>
was initially described as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="True" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[1049,1180,803,837]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Lophuromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="11" pageNumber="608" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aquilus">L. aquilus</taxonomicName>
and then syn- onymized with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1888" box="[1028,1266,843,877]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Lophuromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="11" pageNumber="608" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="flavopunctatus">L. flavopunctatus</taxonomicName>
. G. G. Musser and M. D. Carleton in 2005 and W. N. Verheyen and colleagues in 2002 in their revisionof the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1888" box="[1088,1316,965,994]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Lophuromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="11" pageNumber="608" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="flavopunctatus">L. flavopunctatus</taxonomicName>
species complex sorted out 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1906" box="[1136,1292,1001,1035]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Lophuromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="11" pageNumber="608" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brunneus">L. brunneus</taxonomicName>
based on morphometric and molecular charac-
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[173,1382,1079,1664]" pageId="11" pageNumber="608">
teristics. Genetic distance between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1906" box="[669,826,1079,1113]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Lophuromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="11" pageNumber="608" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brunneus">L. brunneus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1888" box="[901,1126,1079,1113]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Lophuromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="11" pageNumber="608" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="flavopunctatus">L. flavopunctatus</taxonomicName>
is small, and they could be the same species. Nevertheless, pending additional molecular analyses, they are considered distinct here, following A. Monadjem and colleagues in 2015. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[175,860,1197,1231]" pageId="11" pageNumber="608" type="distribution">
<caption box="[175,860,1197,1231]" inLine="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="608" targetBox="[1143,1147,1639,1664]" targetPageId="11">
<paragraph blockId="11.[173,1382,1079,1664]" box="[175,860,1197,1231]" pageId="11" pageNumber="608">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[175,351,1197,1231]" pageId="11" pageNumber="608">Distribution.</emphasis>
W of the Rift Valley in SW Ethiopia.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="608" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[173,1382,1079,1664]" pageId="11" pageNumber="608">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[175,426,1245,1270]" pageId="11" pageNumber="608">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 101-138 mm, tail 55-84 mm, ear 17-20 mm, hindfoot 22.8-26-7 mm; weight 38-76 g. Chromosomal complementis 2n = 68 and FNa = 78.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[175,927,1319,1348]" pageId="11" pageNumber="608" type="biology_ecology">
