<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="608" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="11.[173,1382,1079,1664]" pageId="11" pageNumber="608">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[176,532,1512,1546]" pageId="11" pageNumber="608">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Not assessed on The IUCN Red List. The Ethiopian Brushfurred Rat was considered a synonym of the Buff-spotted Brush-furred Rat (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1888" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Lophuromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="11" pageNumber="608" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="flavopunctatus">L. flavopunctatus</taxonomicName>
), which was classified as Least Concern.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
